======================================
This is the main directory for the GEN_BE Version 0.0.0 source code release.
======================================

How to compile and run?
-----------------------

- In gen_be directory, type 'configure' - this will create a configure.gen_be
  file that has appropriate compile options for the supported computers.

  Note: GEN_BE requires netCDF library. If your netCDF library is installed in
        some odd directory, set environment variable NETCDF before you type
        'configure'. For example,

        setenv NETCDF /usr/local/netcdf-pgi

- GEN_BE requires environmental variable WRFDA_DIR to pinter to a compiled WRFDA 
  directory. For example,

        setenv WRFDA_DIR /ptmp/wrfhelp/WRFDA

- To compile gen_be,

        ./configure [-d]

        ./compile [-j n] gen_be

  All executables are generated under src directory.
